topic.title: Ingress Data Processing Subsystem Registers

field-desc.p: This field specifies a 4-bit quality of service value associated with all memory read operations.
This field corresponds to the value driven on the ACE-Lite AR_QOS_M[3:0] signals during a read operation.
This field specifies cache and interconnect properties association with all memory read operations.
This field specifies a 4-bit quality of service value associated with all memory write operations.
This field corresponds to the value driven on the ACE-Lite AW_QOS_M[3:0] signals during a write operation.
This field specifies cache and interconnect properties association with all memory write operations.
This field specifies the protection properties associated with all memory read operations.
This field specifies the protection properties associated with all memory write operations.

This field controls the operational state of the Ingress DPS. Modifying the value of this field causes the queue to transition to the specified operational state. A transition does not complete until the new operational state is reflected in the State (STATE) field in the corresponding Ingress DPS Status (IDP_STS) register.
A direct transition from the enabled to disabled state is not supported.
Firmware must comprehend the possibility of an autonomous state transition to disabled due to an error.
This field indicates the reason that the Ingress DPS was autonomously disabled. This field is automatically cleared when the Autonomous Disable (AUTDIS) bit in this register is cleared.
This bit is set by hardware when the Ingress DPS is autonomously disabled due to an error.
This field indicates the current operational state of the ingress DSP.
This field is bit 31:16 of the default CRC seed for PI1. It is ignored for PI with 16-bit CRC.
This field is the lower 16 bits of the default CRC Seed for PI1.
This field is bit 63:32 of the default CRC seed for PI2. It is ignored for PI with 16-bit or 32-bit CRC.
This field is bit 47:32 of the default CRC seed for PI2. It is ignored for PI with 16-bit or 32-bit CRC.
This field is bit 31:16 of the default CRC seed for PI2. It is ignored for PI with 16-bit CRC.
This field is the lower 16 bits of the default CRC Seed for PI2.
This field is bit 63:32 of the default CRC seed for PI2. It is ignored for PI with 16-bit or 32-bit CRC.
This field is bit 47:32 of the default CRC seed for PI2. It is ignored for PI with 16-bit or 32-bit CRC.

table.title: IDP_STATSCTL - Ingress DPS Debug Statistics Control

field-desc.p: Writing a 1 will cause real-time statistics to be captured in CSR registers. The real-time statistics will be reset and continue to accumulate
IDP_DBGCTL.debug_en must be set for statistical monitoring to occur

table.title: IDP_STATSSTOPCNT - Ingress DPS Debug Statistics Stop Control

field-desc.p: A non-zero value will automatically stop statistical accumulation the specified number of clocks after the prior stats capture
A stats capture is still required to capture the results into CSR registers
